# Copy to .denylist.local (gitignored) and add one term per line.
# scripts/check-denylist.sh greps staged changes for these terms (case-insensitive,
# fixed strings) and blocks the commit on any match. Keeps personal and
# infrastructure identifiers out of the public repo.
#
# Put the real values ONLY in .denylist.local, never here. Examples of the kinds
# of terms to list (replace with your own):
#
#   <your full name>
#   <your practice name>
#   <your employer name>
#   <your build server hostname / domain>
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
